<HEADLINE>
SHEIK ISA BIN SALMAN AL-KHALIFA, EMIR OF BAHRAIN 
</HEADLINE>
  (See also BAHRAIN-EMIR, filed in category ``i'') 
(js) 
 By DOUGLAS JEHL   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   RIYADH, Saudi Arabia _ The emir of Bahrain, Sheik Isa bin Salman
al-Khalifa, who collapsed and died Saturday at 65, shaped his
country into an important ally of the West during nearly four
decades in power.
