r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BBA-PALMEIRO-INJURY-T     03-07 0287
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BBA-PALMEIRO-INJURY-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
PALMEIRO TO UNDERGO MRI SUNDAY
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By T.R. Sullivan 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   PORT CHARLOTTE, Fla. _ Rafael Palmeiro, feeling more pain in his
right knee, returned to Texas last night for further tests.
</P>
<P>
   Palmeiro is expecting to be examined by Dr. John Conway today
and undergo a magnetic resonance imaging exam.
</P>
<P>
   ``This has never happened to me before so yeah, I'm a little
worried,'' Palmeiro said. ``But not too much, it's just that this
is all new to me. Hopefully it will be the last time.''
</P>
<P>
   Palmeiro felt the pain come back while jogging on Thursday. He
originally injured the knee running the steps at The Ballpark in
Arlington and underwent arthroscopic surgery on Feb. 10. He has
been limited to rehabilitation work and has yet to join the
workouts or play in a game.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're getting to the point where we're concerned,'' Rangers
general manager Doug Melvin said. ``If anything, this might be
something new. We just won't know until he goes back and gets it
re-evaluated.''
</P>
<P>
   Palmeiro is still hoping to start playing in games within a
week, depending on what happens with today's examination.
</P>
<P>
   ``This is just probably part of the rehabilitation process,''
Palmeiro said. ``I'm not sure if this is a setback. I just want to
get it taken care of so I can go on.''
</P>
<P>
   Palmeiro has never been on the disabled list and has played more
games than anybody this decade expect Baltimore third baseman Cal
Ripken.
</P>
<P>
   Lee Stevens has been playing first base during Palmeiro's
absence, but the Rangers are also without Mike Simms. He is
sidelined for 3-4 weeks with a partial tear of his left achilles
tendon.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
