<TEXT>
<P>
   The Seattle Post-Intelligencer plans to move the following
stories for clients of the NYTimes News Service for editions of
Monday, March 8 and thereafter. If you have any questions, please
call Mary Downes on the national-foreign desk at (206) 448-8158.
</P>
<P>
   BKN-SONICS-WOLVES (Seattle) _ The Seattle SuperSonics host the
Minnesota Timberwolves.
</P>
<P>
   By Clare Farnsworth. (Story will move in the ``s'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   BKC-UW-NCAA (Seattle) _ A surprise Sweet Sixteen team last year,
the University of Washington Huskies learn their NCAA tournament
fate Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   By Jim Moore. (Story will move in the ``s'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   BKC-VECSEY-COLUMN (Seattle) _ Column on Washington and the NCAA
tournament.
</P>
<P>
   By Laura Vecsey. (Story will move in the ``s'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   BKC-NCAA-TOURNAMENT (Seattle) _ Eight men's college basketball
