<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LEAH-PERSONALS-SFCHRON </SLUG>
  
By LEAH GARCHIK 
 c. 1999 San Francisco Chronicle 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; A LITTLE NONSURGICAL BUFFALO INTERVENTION &LR;
</P>
<P>
   A giant version of the seal of the Department of the Interior _
snowcapped mountains, a sunset and a buffalo _ was created last
week as a backdrop for  &UR; President Clinton &LR; , who was to speak at a
celebration of the department's 150th anniversary.
</P>
<P>
   Organizers realized upon seeing the seal, says the Washington
Post, that its anatomically correct male buffalo would be right
behind the president. Judicious use of the airbrush created more
prairie and less buffalo. The seals on flags and programs for the
occasion were unaltered.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; MONICA'S LITTLE LIST &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; - Monica Lewinsky &LR;  will reportedly interrupt her European book
tour to be special guest at the Academy Awards party thrown by
Vanity Fair magazine in Los Angeles.
</P>
<P>
   - The ``Thomas'' who got Lewinsky pregnant is said to be
 &UR; Thomas Longstreth &LR; , 42, deputy undersecretary for readiness in the
Defense Department and former legislative assistant for Senator
 &UR; Edward Kennedy &LR; , D-Mass.
</P>
<P>
   -  &UR; Roxanne Seabright &LR;  of Artfibers Gallery in San Francisco, &LR; 
has called to say that a year ago she personally taught  &UR; Barbara &LR; 
 &UR; Lewinsky &LR; , Monica's stepmother, to knit, whereupon Barbara taught
Monica. Lewinsky's book and interview described the solace she has
received from the craft; Seabright recommends knitting as a way to
recover from scandal.
</P>
<P>
   - Site Leader, a company that hawks Internet domains, is
offering www.monicalewinsky.com,  &LR; a site the company says it hopes
is bought by its namesake, to enable her to tell her true story.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; - Marc Huestis &LR;  gave his personal Emmy for most relevant ads
during the interview to Maytag (``gets even the strongest stains
out'') and DiGiorno pizza. Runners-up: Fidelity (insurance),
Discover, Oral-B, Revitalique and the movie ``Forces of Nature.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; - Chris Morano  &LR; counted 40 uses of the word ``relationship,''
less than 10 of ``love'' and one of the word ``mistake.''
</P>
<P>
   _ For the pleasure of art lovers, eBay is auctioning a black
velvet painting of Lewinsky, hand-painted in Tijuana by  &UR; Jorge &LR; 
 &UR; Terrones &LR; ; sets of Bill Clinton-Monica Lewinsky Starr Wars and
Underwear stamps; Clinton/Monica Lovers Nesting Dolls; Bill
Clinton/Monica Lewinsky wooden nickels; Monica Lewinsky $8 bill;
Clinton &AMP; Monica comic book; and Monica Lewinsky Intern Nodder
(bobbing head doll).
</P>
<P>
   In addition,  &UR; Marjorie Wilkinson &LR;  describes ``Elvis Wept,'' a
painting by  &UR; Johnny Ace &LR; : ``American flag background, Bill leering
at Monica and the two of them being watched by Elvis, standing off
to the left, looking pained, a 3-D plastic tear coming from his
eye.''
</P>
<P>
   - ``Monica's Untold Story: An Amorality Tale'' (Regan; $12) is
by poet and cartoonist  &UR; Bill Plympton &LR; . A sample couplet about the
couple: ``I never knew that it was wrong/ to dance and prance and
flash my thong.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; REMEMBERING &LR;
</P>
<P>
   -  &UR; Al Gore &LR;  was the featured speaker Sunday at a Shoah
Foundation screening in Washington of ``The Last Days,'' the
 &UR; Steven Spielberg &LR; -funded documentary about the Holocaust in
Hungary. Representative  &UR; Tom Lantos &LR; , D-San Mateo, and the other
four Holocaust survivors featured in the film attended the showing.
- Learning last week of the death of  &UR; Dusty &LR; 
 &UR; Springfield &LR; ,  &UR; Jim Thompson &LR; , who lives in San Francisco now but
owned a nightclub in Stockton-on-Tees in northern England in the
early '60s, recalled their friendship.
</P>
<P>
   Springfield came to town to play one supper club, while
 &UR; Shirley &LR; 
 &UR; Bassey &LR;  was appearing at another, and local papers reported that
Bassey was getting paid much more. Intending to razz Bassey about
the money, Springfield took Thompson along to her rival's show.
</P>
<P>
   Although Springfield's lifestyle at the time was considered
radical _ being found in bed with her black female lover caused her
to be thrown out of a local hotel _ she was so nervous about hazing
her rival, recalls Thompson, that she tore her bread to shreds;
afterwards &LR; , club management refused to let her into Bassey's
dressing room.
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Mackenzie Phillips  &LR; recalls in next week's TV Guide the time
she was 18 and  &UR; Mick Jagger &LR;  invited her and her father,  &UR; John &LR; 
 &UR; Phillips &LR; , over for sandwiches: Jagger sent Papa John out for
mayonnaise, locked the door, told her he'd been ``waiting for this
since you were 10 years old'' and took her to bed. She said she
still thinks he's sexy.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ``(Bruce Willis) is so supertough that it seems ridiculous, &LR; 
 &UR; like a butch lesbian who tries to be supermacho but always &LR; 
 &UR; collides with her own soft side.'' &LR;
</P>
<P>
   -  &UR; Manuela Kay &LR; ,  &LR; curator of a Berlin Gay Museum show about 20th
century gay icons, quoted in the Advocate.
</P>
</TEXT>
