<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-07 18:48 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A0951 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-GEN-YESTERDAY-LADN-(S     03-07 0344
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-GEN-YESTERDAY-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
LONGDON FINISHES WITH WIN, HARRICK WITH LOSS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ As the year 2000 approaches, here's a look at some
of the interesting anniversaries that will occur this week in Los
Angeles sports history !ital!(followed by the ranking of the event
from the book ``Unforgettable: The 100 Greatest Moments in Los
Angeles Sports History'' in parenthesis):
</P>
<P>
   __ March 9, 1986: Attracting 10,787 runners, the largest ever
for a first-time marathon, the City of Los Angeles Marathon is
launched. Two Americans win the first race _ Rick Sayre (2:12:50)
and Nancy Ditz (2:36:27) _ and each win $10,000 and a car.
</P>
<P>
   __ March 11, 1933: During an exhibition game at Wrigley Field in
South-Central L.A., an earthquake sends all members of the New York
Giants and Chicago Cubs scurrying out of dugouts and toward second
base until the tremors stop.
</P>
<P>
   __ March 11, 1980: In a game against the Lakers, San Diego
Clippers center Bill Walton injures his foot. He wouldn't play in
the NBA again for 2{ years.
</P>
<P>
   __ March 12, 1966: Johnny Longden wins his final race at age 59
with George Royal in the San Juan Capistrano Handicap at Santa
Anita before 60,792. It is his 6,032nd victory in a career of
32,413 races spanning 40 years. !ital!(74)
</P>
<P>
   __ March 13, 1986: Lakers guard Magic Johnson hands out his
5,000th career assist.
</P>
<P>
   __ March 14, 1996: Defending national champion UCLA loses to
Pete Carril's Princeton squad 43-41 in the opening round of the
NCAA basketball tournament. It would turn out to be the final game
for coach Jim Harrick, fired before the start of the next season.
</P>
<P>
   __ Birthdays: Tuesday: Former UCLA soccer star Paul Caliguiri
(35). Wednesday: Former Dodgers reliever Steve Howe (41) and former
USC star offensive tackle and NFL Hall of Famer Ron Mix (61).
Friday: Dodgers outfielder Raul Mondesi (28) and former Dodgers
outfielder Darryl Strawberry (37). Sunday: Dodgers pitcher Kevin
Brown (34).
</P>
