<HEADLINE>
ANGER IN CONGRESS 
</HEADLINE>
  (lh) 
 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ Republican leaders said Sunday that the report that
the Chinese had obtained U.S. nuclear secrets could make it
difficult for the United States to support Beijing's efforts to
gain entry into the World Trade Organization.
</P>
<P>
   In talks in Beijing last week, Albright was encouraging to the
Chinese about their prospects for joining the trade group, although
China has done little to meet international demands that it do more
to open its market to imports.
</P>
</TEXT>
