<HEADLINE>
JERRO NAMED PERMANENT COACH
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By LEE BARNATHAN  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ One other piece of business was settled Sunday:
Frozena Jerro had the interim label removed. She is now Cal State
Northridge's head women's basketball coach.
</P>
<P>
   The announcement, made by interim athletic director San
Jankovich and outgoing President Blenda Wilson, came moments after
the team learned it would play at Colorado State in the first round
of the NCAA Tournament.
</P>
<P>
   Jankovich said he and Wilson met Saturday night after Northridge
won the Big Sky Conference tournamentand decided it should be done.
</P>
<P>
   Jerro and the team learned about it at the moment of the
announcement. As a result, guard Edniesha Curry, who had hinted she
might leave Northridge if Jerro weren't named head coach, said she
will stay for her remaining two seasons.
</P>
</TEXT>
