<HEADLINE>
EXECUTIVE NOMINATED FOR TIMES CO. BOARD 
</HEADLINE>
  (sw) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   The board of The New York Times Co. has nominated Henry B.
Schacht, former chairman and chief executive of Lucent Technologies
Inc., for election as a director at the Times Co.'s annual
shareholder meeting on April 15.
</P>
<P>
   Schacht, 64, retired last year as chairman of Lucent, the
communications-equipment maker, based in Murray Hill, N.J., that
was spun off from the AT&AMP;T Corp. in 1996. He had stepped down as
chief executive in 1997. Before joining Lucent in 1995, Schacht had
been chairman and chief executive of the Cummins Engine Company,
which he first joined in 1964 as a vice president.
</P>
<P>
   Last month, the Times Co. announced that Raul E. Cesan, the
president and chief operating officer of the Schering-Plough Corp.,
had also been nominated for election as a director at the
shareholder meeting next month. Two current directors, William O.
Taylor and George L. Shinn, are retiring.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
