<HEADLINE>
WINNER RESPECTS EARNHARDT'S EFFORT 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By MARK ARMIJO  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LAS VEGAS _  &UR; Jeff Burton not only engaged his older brother,
 &UR; Ward, in a tense, late-race shootout, he and  &UR; Dale Earnhardt also
locked horns during the Las Vegas 400 on Sunday at Las Vegas Motor
Speedway.
</P>
<P>
   Twice, when Jeff Burton was leading, he tried to put the
resourceful Earnhardt a lap down.
</P>
<P>
   And twice he failed.
</P>
<P>
   ``Don't anybody think that Earnhardt's laying down and not
racing because he is,'' Jeff Burton said. ``I think Dale Earnhardt
is still one of the best drivers in Winston Cup racing. He's not a
seven-time champion because he's not a hard racer.
</P>
<P>
   ``Dale Earnhardt did what I would have done if I was in his
shoes and trying to stay on the lead lap. He ran me clean, and he
never did anything that was wrong.
</P>
<P>
   ``A lot of people think that he's forgotten how to race and he's
not as sharp as he used to be, but I tell you, when the chips are
down and he sits in a car that's as fast as anybody else's, he's
real hard to beat.''
</P>
<P>
   The gritty Earnhardt was rewarded with seventh place.
</P>
<P>
   ``We had to race hard a couple of times to stay on the lead lap,
but it paid off,'' Earnhardt said. ``All in all, it was a pretty
good day. But we've got to get better.'' &QL; 
Send in the clowns &QL; 
Ward Burton almost took himself out of contention early by spinning
into the grassy infield while entering pit road on Lap 57.
</P>
<P>
   ``I just came in too fast,'' Burton said. ``But even when I went
through the grass like a clown out there, we still came out leading
the race.'' &QL; 
Bumper cars &QL; 
Three of the five caution flags were produced by accidents. There
were no serious injuries, but a crash on Lap 132 left eight
vehicles in worse shape than they were on Lap 131.
</P>
<P>
   The melee was triggered by  &UR; Kenny Irwin, whose car wiggled, then
collected  &UR; Kenny Wallace, who slammed into the outside retaining
wall on the back straightaway.
</P>
<P>
   ``Kenny Irwin lost it and hit me in the left side and wrecked us
both,'' Wallace said. ``That's racing. It's discouraging.''
</P>
<P>
   ``I just got loose on new tires,'' Irwin said. &QL; 
Pit stops &QL; 
The last time Jeff and Ward Burton finished first and second, it
was in a NASCAR Busch Series race in 1993.
</P>
<P>
   In last year's inaugural race, Ford Taurus drivers captured 13
of the top 14 positions. Although Jeff Burton won in a Ford, the
next highest finishing Ford was  &UR; Rusty Wallace, who was ninth. Only
five of the top 14 finishers were in Fords.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Mike Skinner stretched his lead in the drivers standings to 51
points over Rusty Wallace. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
