<SLUG> BC-OBIT-GOLDBERG-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
RICHARD GOLDBERG, CONTRACT BRIDGE LEAGUE EXECUTIVE, DIES AT 76 
</HEADLINE>
  (sw) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Richard Goldberg, a longtime executive of the American Contract
Bridge League, died on Sunday at his home in Nashville, Tenn. He
was 76.
</P>
<P>
   He died after suffering a heart attack, said his daughter, Joan
Conroy, also of Nashville.
</P>
<P>
   Goldberg was executive secretary and general manager of the
American Contract Bridge League from 1971 to 1984. From 1963 to
1971, he supervised the league's tournament division.
</P>
<P>
   He later served the World Bridge Federation as a delegate from
the American league, then as secretary, treasurer and financial
director.
</P>
<P>
   He was educated at Vanderbilt University, and he served in the
Navy at the close of World War II.
</P>
<P>
   In addition to his daughter, he is survived by his wife,
Frederica; a son, Richard Jr., of Plano, Texas; another daughter,
Geraldine Goldberg of Arcata, Calif., and six grandchildren.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
