alternative life. (Fred R. Conrad/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT1) THREE MILE ISLAND, Pa. -- March 06, 1999 --
NUCLEAR-POWER-REVIEW, 03-07 -- The meltdown at Three Mile Island 20
years ago set off a crisis in nuclear power. Today, half the plant
is running and half remains shut. Nationwide, reactors are quietly
producing about one-quarter more electricity each, and the level of
radiation exposure to workers is down, as is the number of
automatic shut-downs. (Keith Meyers/New York Times Photo)
</P>
